article.headline: North Texas 79, New Orleans 77
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Collin Dennis' 24 points included the layup with three seconds left that lifted North Texas over New Orleans 79-77 on Saturday. UNO (18-12, 8-10 Sun Belt) led 71-66 with 2:31 to play, but North Texas (18-12, 8-10) got a layup from Quincy Williams and a 3-pointer from Ben Bell to tie it at 71. The Mean Green went ahead again, but Bo McCalebb hit two free throws with 6.7 lefts to tie it at 77-all. After Dennis' final basket, he bounced a layup off the glass from halfcourt. A layup by UNO's Kyndall Dykes rimmed out at the buzzer. Quincy Williams had 15 points and 11 rebounds for North Texas, which had a 38-29 rebounding advantage. McCalebb led the Privateers with 23 points and seven assists, and James Parlow had 14 points -- 12 in the second half. Dykes also had 14 points on 6-of-10 shooting.
